    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nI want a cool transparent terminal in neovide, so I set winblend=100 in neovim. The cursor in the terminal is not longer visible.\r\n\r\n~~I'm using floaterm as the floating terminal. Reporting here because I think it uses the same rendering code as neovim's built-in teminal (non-floating)~~\r\nI have found a way to make a floating terminal in vanilla nvim, which is what I've written in \"Steps to reproduce\"\r\n\r\nHere it is with winblend=100 (gnome-terminal, alacritty, kitty, neovide):\r\n![Screenshot from 2024-09-02 19-11-44](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/48ca9517-49af-48f4-9275-371b0afc295e)\r\n\r\nAnd with winblend=50:\r\n![Screenshot from 2024-09-02 19-12-17](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f3a99fd8-fda2-42c6-a766-4287960a8f1c)\r\n\r\n(The screenshots are made with floaterm, but the same thing happens in vanilla nvim)\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nconfig.vim\r\n```\r\nfunction! Floatbuffer() abort\r\n    \" Define the size of the floating window\r\n    let width = 50\r\n    let height = 25\r\n\r\n    set winblend=100\r\n\r\n    \" Create the scratch buffer displayed in the floating window\r\n    let buf = nvim_create_buf(v:false, v:true)\r\n\r\n    \" Get the current UI\r\n    let ui = nvim_list_uis()[0]\r\n\r\n    \" Create the floating window\r\n    let opts = {'relative': 'editor',\r\n                \\ 'width': width,\r\n                \\ 'height': height,\r\n                \\ 'col': (ui.width/2) - (width/2),\r\n                \\ 'row': (ui.height/2) - (height/2),\r\n                \\ 'anchor': 'NW',\r\n                \\ 'style': 'minimal',\r\n                \\ }\r\n    let win = nvim_open_win(buf, 1, opts)\r\nendfunction\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim -u config.vim\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n:call Floatbuffer()\r\n:term\r\n<i>\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe cursor vanishes\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe cursor should have the same opacity regardless of winblend. (Is is intentional?)\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.1 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1713773202\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno, vim doesn't have winblend\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nNixOS unstable\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nGnome Terminal, kitty, alacritty, neovide\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nnixpkgs (nixvim)",
